SIMPLE: needful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Needful
<hw>Need"ful</hw> <pr>(n⟦emac⟧d"f⟦usdot⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of need; in need or want; needy;
distressing.</def> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>needful</qex> time of trouble.</q> <rj><qau>Bk. of Com.
Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Necessary for supply or relief; requisite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All things <qex>needful</qex> for defense abound.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Need"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Need"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Needily</ent>⟦br⟧
